This is huge.

43:45.356 --> 43:47.490
It's gargantuan, huh?

43:47.492 --> 43:49.258
Oh hi, sweetie.

43:50.161 --> 43:51.360
Run!

44:14.185 --> 44:15.685
Fuck you, Harvey!

44:18.289 --> 44:20.022
Holy fuck!

44:33.972 --> 44:36.739
Never tell a girl you
wrote a book about her,

44:36.741 --> 44:37.940
even if you did.

44:37.942 --> 44:39.342
That's my advice to you, pal.

44:41.045 --> 44:42.345
Oh man.

44:45.216 --> 44:48.050
Jesus man, what the hell.

44:48.052 --> 44:49.318
What the hell?

44:49.320 --> 44:50.553
- Yeah.
- I'm the one

44:50.555 --> 44:52.288
who should be asking
that question.

44:52.290 --> 44:55.992
Okay look, I would never
have sent you into that house

44:55.994 --> 44:57.960
if I had known that
woman had a gun.

44:57.962 --> 45:01.230
I promise I never
would have, ever.

45:01.232 --> 45:03.599
We almost fucking
died back there, died,

45:03.601 --> 45:05.234
and for what, a suit?

45:05.236 --> 45:08.204
Yeah, a very
expensive suit, man.

45:09.340 --> 45:10.473
I quit.

45:10.475 --> 45:11.741
You can't quit,
there's no where to go,

45:11.743 --> 45:13.276
you're in the middle of nowhere.

45:13.278 --> 45:16.712
This is fucking insane I'm
not doing this for $100 a day.

45:18.917 --> 45:22.285
Okay, okay, I'll make it $150.

45:22.287 --> 45:24.153
That's not why
I took this job.

45:24.923 --> 45:26.689
Okay.

45:28.293 --> 45:29.792
What do you want?

45:29.794 --> 45:31.694
I just want you to read my
short story and give me notes

45:31.696 --> 45:33.596
on it to help me
become a better writer.

45:33.598 --> 45:36.032
Writers get better by
writing, there you go.

45:37.936 --> 45:39.402
Then I guess you peaked.

45:46.311 --> 45:47.376
All right.

45:48.947 --> 45:50.680
All right, I'll read your story.

45:53.985 --> 45:55.117
I'll read your story.

45:57.222 --> 45:58.888
You don't believe me?

45:58.890 --> 46:00.022
Here, pass it over.

46:01.693 --> 46:04.193
I'll read it tonight at
the motel, I promise.

46:09.167 --> 46:10.399
Thank you very much.

48:42.286 --> 48:43.519
Testing, test.

49:19.357 --> 49:21.057
How much time we got, Greg?

49:21.059 --> 49:22.491
You're already
15 minutes late.

49:22.493 --> 49:23.325
Perfect.

49:31.702 --> 49:33.369
I want you to go see how
many people are sitting

49:33.371 --> 49:34.770
in those chairs.

49:43.281 --> 49:46.449
Please welcome
Mr. Harvard Wolworth McCoy.

50:00.231 --> 50:05.367
Well hello
everyone.

50:05.369 --> 50:08.270
I'd like to thank you
all for coming out.

50:08.272 --> 50:11.807
It's very hard to believe
that "The Grand Affliction"

50:11.809 --> 50:13.476
is 15 years old.

50:15.580 --> 50:19.315
I've been asked to do a Q
and A, but I'm gonna forgo

50:19.317 --> 50:22.785
that for the time being,
because my friend here asked

50:22.787 --> 50:24.954
for me to read a
special passage.

50:24.956 --> 50:28.924
I don't mind saying it's
a difficult passage,

50:28.926 --> 50:30.392
and I'll be frank,

50:32.463 --> 50:34.463
it's a painful passage.

50:34.465 --> 50:35.397
So bear with me.

50:54.852 --> 50:55.651
Name?

50:55.653 --> 50:56.785
Lauren.

50:56.787 --> 50:58.087
Lorraine.

50:58.089 --> 50:59.155
Lauren.

50:59.157 --> 51:01.257
There you go, thank you.

51:01.259 --> 51:02.658
I love your book.

51:02.660 --> 51:04.093
Oh thank you very much.

51:04.095 --> 51:05.361
I wrote a paper on it.

51:05.363 --> 51:06.962
No kidding!

51:06.964 --> 51:08.664
I'm very flattered,
what's your name?

51:08.666 --> 51:09.532
Dan.

51:11.369 --> 51:12.434
There you go, Dan.

51:12.436 --> 51:13.202
Thank you.

51:13.204 --> 51:15.204
Have a good day.

51:15.206 --> 51:16.372
Harvey McCoy.

51:17.675 --> 51:19.208
Do I know you?

51:19.210 --> 51:22.344
Probably, I'm a reporter
for the local paper.

51:22.346 --> 51:25.281
I was hoping you'd be open
to answering a few questions.

51:25.283 --> 51:28.450
Look, press questions
go through my agent.

51:28.452 --> 51:30.286
Hey, what just
happened in there?

51:30.288 --> 51:32.688
Don't worry, this
isn't about the book.

51:33.991 --> 51:36.358
Oh, I'm answering questions
only about the book.

51:38.462 --> 51:39.295
Fine.

51:40.631 --> 51:43.566
What about the
inspiration behind the book?

52:05.756 --> 52:06.755
Let's go.

53:06.150 --> 53:07.616
I have a daughter.

53:09.253 --> 53:12.321
I saw a picture
on your mantle.

53:12.323 --> 53:13.155
Yeah, hm.

53:20.298 --> 53:21.163
Where is she?

53:28.306 --> 53:29.905
I was a good father.

53:29.907 --> 53:32.641
I was a good father, for a
few years I was a good father.

53:34.178 --> 53:36.979
It was something I wanted to
be, I made the commitment.

53:39.750 --> 53:41.650
I loved her, she loved
me, I was her whole world,

53:41.652 --> 53:42.918
she was my whole world.

53:44.422 --> 53:46.021
And when they're that age
and they look up at you,

53:46.023 --> 53:50.326
they don't want anything from
you but for you to love them

53:50.328 --> 53:52.428
and I did, I loved
her and she loved me.

53:55.466 --> 53:57.266
Which is fine, but I wasn't
totally getting along

53:57.268 --> 53:58.534
with her mother.

53:59.603 --> 54:01.403
We were living together,
we were married.

54:03.274 --> 54:08.344
Anyway, so I got this, my first
big, my first big book deal.

54:10.214 --> 54:12.848
And it was a big deal
to me, and I thought,

54:12.850 --> 54:16.352
"Man, I better take this
seriously and I've gotta put

54:16.354 --> 54:17.853
some time into it."

54:17.855 --> 54:21.190
And I put all this time into
and that took time away from,

54:22.626 --> 54:26.261
from her and my marriage.

54:27.498 --> 54:29.665
You know, it's not an
uncommon story, right,

54:29.667 --> 54:33.235
when you just head off
in different directions.

54:33.237 --> 54:36.372
And, you know, I knew
it was coming to an end,

54:36.374 --> 54:37.206
so did she.

54:38.576 --> 54:42.978
And we separated, and for
awhile it wasn't all that bad,

54:42.980 --> 54:43.812
it was...

54:46.150 --> 54:50.252
It was manageable, you
know, like it wasn't ideal

54:50.254 --> 54:53.155
it wasn't the dream,
it was just manageable.

54:55.226 --> 54:57.493
But to cope with it,

54:58.863 --> 55:00.496
man I started drinking.

55:02.400 --> 55:04.099
I started drinking real heavy.

55:05.369 --> 55:08.837
And that just uh, I
just turned everything

55:08.839 --> 55:10.072
into a giant mess.

55:13.177 --> 55:16.311
So, I couldn't visit anymore,

55:18.249 --> 55:20.416
she didn't want me to come
around, because of things

55:20.418 --> 55:22.217
that happened that I'm
not even gonna go into

55:22.219 --> 55:24.620
that frankly, I don't
even remember, not really.

55:26.223 --> 55:27.523
I don't remember everything.

55:29.960 --> 55:31.760
But I always remember
her birthday.

55:34.932 --> 55:37.299
I needed that connection,
I needed to feel

55:39.236 --> 55:40.869
I had a connection with her.

55:44.241 --> 55:46.408
And I looked for it on her
birthday's, and when her

55:46.410 --> 55:48.143
fifth birthday came around

55:52.116 --> 55:54.216
her mother didn't
want me to see her.

55:54.218 --> 55:56.552
That was the thing, she
was not gonna let me see

55:58.389 --> 56:00.489
my own daughter on her fifth,

56:01.959 --> 56:04.893
fifth birthday, which
honestly I understood.

56:04.895 --> 56:08.897
At the time when she said
that, as pissed as I was,

56:11.402 --> 56:12.734
I understood why.

56:18.175 --> 56:20.342
So on the day of her
birthday I drank.

56:20.344 --> 56:21.810
I got up early

56:25.082 --> 56:26.849
and I drank a hell of a
lot and I got hammered,

56:26.851 --> 56:29.518
I got blackout drunk.

56:33.657 --> 56:37.326
And the next thing
I know

56:40.097 --> 56:41.530
next thing I know,

56:44.702 --> 56:47.336
I was wrapped around the
tree out front of the house.

56:50.140 --> 56:51.173
Totaled the car.

56:52.810 --> 56:54.843
And there were kids, it
was a birthday party,

56:54.845 --> 56:56.945
so there's kids coming
in and out of the,

56:59.884 --> 57:02.417
my daughter was coming
in and out of the house.

57:07.324 --> 57:09.191
And that was it,
I'd finished it.

57:12.997 --> 57:15.731
I was never to be
forgiven for that.

57:17.501 --> 57:18.300
And again,

57:20.337 --> 57:21.370
I knew why.

57:27.378 --> 57:30.712
As horrible as it looked, it
was as horrible as I felt.

57:32.917 --> 57:36.451
And I knew that I had
lost, I'd lost them.

57:38.422 --> 57:40.822
It's not something
you can accept really,

57:40.824 --> 57:45.327
so what I did was, I thought
to myself, "There's gotta

57:45.329 --> 57:47.930
be a way that I can make this,

57:47.932 --> 57:50.399
some way that I can make this,

57:51.869 --> 57:54.736
some way I could make it okay."

57:54.738 --> 57:58.507
You know, manageable
again, normal again.

58:00.744 --> 58:03.445
So I did the smart
thing, I quit drinking.

58:03.447 --> 58:04.479
I stopped drinkin.

58:05.516 --> 58:08.917
Which was a big deal
and wasn't easy.

58:11.221 --> 58:16.291
And uh, the next thing I
thought I had to do was,

58:17.061 --> 58:19.361
well I'm gonna write that book.

58:22.967 --> 58:23.832
And I did.

58:26.637 --> 58:28.670
It wasn't the book
the publisher wanted,

58:29.473 --> 58:30.839
but a different book.

58:32.643 --> 58:34.776
But luckily he liked
it, he loved it.

58:35.946 --> 58:38.246
And so did other people,
because it ended up on

58:38.248 --> 58:42.317
the New York Times best
selling list, as I like to say.

58:45.656 --> 58:48.457
But that book,
that 300 page book,

58:54.431 --> 58:56.865
was meant for one person only,

58:58.268 --> 58:59.134
meant for Hannah.

59:02.740 --> 59:04.373
So that she could

59:06.577 --> 59:07.976
see how I felt,

59:10.347 --> 59:11.847
hear my apology,

59:14.418 --> 59:17.352
and understand that
this is important to me.

59:17.354 --> 59:21.423
That she understood that I knew

59:23.661 --> 59:27.396
I had, I had ruined
her first family,

59:30.868 --> 59:35.937
and that maybe this was a
place to start from, this book.

59:37.775 --> 59:39.474
Because I was never gonna
reach her, I was never

59:39.476 --> 59:41.009
gonna get a card to her,
I was never gonna get

59:41.011 --> 59:42.344
a phone call to her.

59:42.346 --> 59:44.546
I didn't even know for
a long period of time,

59:46.150 --> 59:48.183
where they were living.

59:50.854 --> 59:52.187
But if I put a book out,

59:54.458 --> 59:57.492
it's out there forever,
she'll find it one day

59:57.494 --> 59:59.227
and she'll read it.

59:59.229 --> 01:00:00.195
And it's dedicated

01:00:03.867 --> 01:00:04.766
to Hannah McCoy.

01:00:10.407 --> 01:00:13.408
But she didn't read it,
or at least if she did

01:00:17.147 --> 01:00:19.414
I guess it didn't
mean much to her,

01:00:21.919 --> 01:00:25.987
because I never heard from
her or her mother again,

01:00:27.324 --> 01:00:29.391
for 15 years,

01:00:30.861 --> 01:00:31.727
16 years.

01:00:36.867 --> 01:00:41.837
So I decided that the next
best thing I could do,

01:00:45.042 --> 01:00:48.410
because I knew, the only
thing I knew about her

01:00:48.412 --> 01:00:49.745
was that she lives in

01:00:51.882 --> 01:00:52.681
Owen Sound.

01:00:55.285 --> 01:00:57.185
- The last stop.
- The last stop.

01:00:58.756 --> 01:01:00.789
That's what this
whole thing is about.

01:01:00.791 --> 01:01:04.426
This what everything is about,
I sank in my very last penny,

01:01:05.896 --> 01:01:07.896
I made sure my name
was in the newspapers,

01:01:07.898 --> 01:01:09.297
I did the interviews,

01:01:13.303 --> 01:01:16.538
because I thought if
she knew I was here

01:01:20.310 --> 01:01:24.479
then maybe, you know
maybe, maybe she comes.

01:01:28.552 --> 01:01:30.285
I don't think she's gonna come.

01:01:31.421 --> 01:01:36.391
I mean, I don't think
this is the right move.

01:01:39.296 --> 01:01:41.496
I just can't accept this.

01:01:48.906 --> 01:01:52.707
This is the stupidest
fucking idea I ever had.

01:01:54.478 --> 01:01:56.011
I don't think it's stupid.

01:01:56.780 --> 01:01:59.381
No?

01:02:03.520 --> 01:02:06.488
All right, I'm gonna go
outside and get some fresh air.

01:02:12.362 --> 01:02:16.698
Hm, don't stay up all night
on that thing, all right?

01:02:19.002 --> 01:02:21.102
I think tomorrow's
gonna be a good one.

01:02:23.006 --> 01:02:24.539
I hope you're right, kid.

01:03:50.894 --> 01:03:52.193
Hey, Mom.

01:03:52.195 --> 01:03:52.928
Where
the hell are you?

01:03:52.930 --> 01:03:53.929
Are you running away?

01:03:53.931 --> 01:03:54.729
What?

01:03:54.731 --> 01:03:56.398
No I'm not running away.

01:03:56.400 --> 01:03:57.632
There's over 20
charges on my credit card,

01:03:57.634 --> 01:03:59.367
- what are doing?
- How many charges?

01:03:59.369 --> 01:04:02.771
Yes, you racked
up over $2,000 on my card!

01:04:02.773 --> 01:04:05.073
I thought I left the
credit card at Harvey's.

01:04:05.075 --> 01:04:06.441
I am calling
the police right now,

01:04:06.443 --> 01:04:08.310
and I'm coming to get you.

01:04:08.312 --> 01:04:11.046
No, Mom, don't call anyone,
I know how to fix this.

01:04:11.048 --> 01:04:13.214
I warned you about
this fucking guy, Greg.

01:04:13.216 --> 01:04:15.083
Mom, it's okay, I
love you good bye.

01:04:15.085 --> 01:04:16.885
No, Greg, do
not hang up the phone.

01:04:31.101 --> 01:04:32.467
Who the fuck are you?

01:04:32.469 --> 01:04:33.468
Fucking, Greg!

01:04:34.604 --> 01:04:36.004
Look, Greg, I think
you got the wrong room.

01:04:36.006 --> 01:04:38.006
No, I've got the right one.

01:04:38.008 --> 01:04:39.341
Oh fuck!

01:04:39.343 --> 01:04:40.275
Where the fuck is my
mom's credit card, Harvey?

01:04:40.277 --> 01:04:41.309
Hey!

01:04:41.311 --> 01:04:42.610
Hey, really?

01:04:42.612 --> 01:04:45.013
Greg, I don't have
your mom's credit card.

01:04:45.015 --> 01:04:46.781
I don't know what you're
talking about, get off me.

01:04:48.618 --> 01:04:50.118
Ow, ow.

01:04:50.120 --> 01:04:52.120
What the fuck is this?

01:04:52.122 --> 01:04:54.055
I'll tell you
what this is, Grego,

01:04:56.126 --> 01:04:58.994
that's my credit card my name
is Wendy Giggles.

01:04:58.996 --> 01:05:00.996
Shut the fuck up, Harvey.

01:05:00.998 --> 01:05:02.330
I don't think that's her
name, I don't think that's

01:05:02.332 --> 01:05:03.365
her real name.

01:06:01.425 --> 01:06:03.091
Greg.

01:06:03.093 --> 01:06:04.826
I'd like to talk.

01:06:04.828 --> 01:06:07.429
What could you possibly
have to say to me right now?

01:06:08.765 --> 01:06:11.332
Well, thank
you for finding me.

01:06:12.402 --> 01:06:14.803
That's it, not sorry?

01:06:16.273 --> 01:06:17.839
What the fuck are you
thinking in there?

01:06:17.841 --> 01:06:19.507
Your biggest event is
tomorrow and you're drinking

01:06:19.509 --> 01:06:20.742
yourself stupid?

01:06:24.915 --> 01:06:26.915
Everything you've
put towards this

01:06:28.351 --> 01:06:31.519
is shot now, do you not
give a fuck about anything?

01:06:34.224 --> 01:06:36.124
I thought this was
for your daughter.

01:06:36.960 --> 01:06:38.159
Or was that even true?

01:06:39.396 --> 01:06:42.097
I would never lie
about her, Greg.

01:06:42.099 --> 01:06:44.365
I don't know to what
extent you'd lie anymore

01:06:44.367 --> 01:06:45.300
to get what you want.

01:06:51.374 --> 01:06:54.242
What everyone says
about you is true,

01:06:54.244 --> 01:06:55.810
you're a washed up asshole.

01:07:04.087 --> 01:07:05.120
What are you doing?

01:07:08.592 --> 01:07:10.925
I think I'm having
a heart attack, Greg.

01:07:10.927 --> 01:07:12.894
What, a heart attack?

01:07:26.243 --> 01:07:27.976
Hello,
911 what's your emergency?

01:07:27.978 --> 01:07:30.245
Hello, I think my boss
is having a heart attack.

01:07:30.247 --> 01:07:32.447
Okay, is he breathing?

01:07:32.449 --> 01:07:34.415
Yeah, he's conscious.

01:07:34.417 --> 01:07:36.151
What's your location?

01:07:36.153 --> 01:07:38.953
We're at
the Traveler's Motel.

01:07:38.955 --> 01:07:40.355
Okay, stay
with me, we have someone

01:07:40.357 --> 01:07:41.489
on the way.

01:08:05.048 --> 01:08:06.447
Is he gonna be okay?

01:08:06.449 --> 01:08:10.051
You
called us just in time.

01:09:27.564 --> 01:09:30.231
No offense, but
this Greg protagonist

01:09:30.233 --> 01:09:32.233
is so unlikeable.

01:09:32.234 --> 01:09:34.135
He's really
the shell of a human.

01:09:34.136 --> 01:09:36.638
He was just
frustratingly passive.

01:09:36.640 --> 01:09:38.706
Okay, your
story was jarring,

01:09:38.707 --> 01:09:40.942
there's no passion
behind your work.

01:09:40.944 --> 01:09:42.277
I'm so sorry.

01:09:42.279 --> 01:09:43.711
It just
doesn't seem like

01:09:43.712 --> 01:09:46.214
it's coming from anywhere
that feels real right now.

01:09:46.216 --> 01:09:48.116
It's just one school.

01:09:48.118 --> 01:09:49.450
You got
to make it about you.

01:09:49.452 --> 01:09:51.752
Hey how's it
going, this is Greg Gifford.

01:09:51.755 --> 01:09:53.321
I too, as well, write.

01:09:53.323 --> 01:09:54.622
I am a writer.

01:09:54.624 --> 01:09:55.657
So what do
you write about, Craig?

01:09:55.659 --> 01:09:58.126
What are your demons?

01:09:58.128 --> 01:09:59.494
What are these?

01:09:59.496 --> 01:10:01.396
Isolation, it's the distraction

01:10:01.398 --> 01:10:04.465
that's the problem,
is distraction.

01:10:04.467 --> 01:10:07.835
There's no such thing
as writers block.

01:10:09.272 --> 01:10:10.638
Distraction...

01:10:10.640 --> 01:10:12.273
Distraction.

01:12:01.418 --> 01:12:02.617
You waited for me.

01:12:02.619 --> 01:12:03.551
You gotta be
fucking kidding me.

01:12:03.553 --> 01:12:05.119
I never doubted you kid.

01:12:05.121 --> 01:12:06.888
Fuck off, Harvey.

01:12:06.890 --> 01:12:07.789
Greg, please.

01:12:08.858 --> 01:12:10.224
You just had a
fucking heart attack,

01:12:10.226 --> 01:12:11.259
what are you doing here?

01:12:11.261 --> 01:12:12.693
Exactly.

01:12:12.695 --> 01:12:15.430
And the only reason I am
here is because of you, man.

01:12:17.567 --> 01:12:19.300
Look, I know maybe
I've been a bit,

01:12:20.437 --> 01:12:21.803
I've been a bit unreliable.

01:12:21.805 --> 01:12:23.237
Unreliable?

01:12:23.239 --> 01:12:25.606
Yeah, maybe you're still
pissed off about the whole

01:12:25.608 --> 01:12:28.876
mom Visa thing, but this
heart attack has shown me

01:12:28.878 --> 01:12:31.746
that maybe I don't got
a lot of chances left

01:12:31.748 --> 01:12:33.014
to say I'm sorry,

01:12:34.250 --> 01:12:36.651
and Greg, I'm sorry.

01:12:38.888 --> 01:12:40.455
Buddy, you're my lucky suit.

