book "The Grand Affliction".

01:18:03.279 --> 01:18:07.248
So without further ado,
I'd like to introduce

01:18:07.250 --> 01:18:08.315
Harvey McCoy.

01:18:27.470 --> 01:18:28.402
Hello everyone.

01:18:29.572 --> 01:18:31.405
I wanna thank you
all for coming.

01:18:32.575 --> 01:18:34.742
I'm very excited
to be here myself.

01:18:36.245 --> 01:18:40.581
15 years ago I wrote a book
called "The Grand Affliction",

01:18:41.818 --> 01:18:43.818
it was written for my daughter,

01:18:45.588 --> 01:18:46.420
Hannah.

01:18:48.357 --> 01:18:51.759
I didn't ever get the
chance to know her

01:18:52.962 --> 01:18:54.495
and that is my regret.

01:18:57.200 --> 01:18:58.432
And that is my book.

01:19:01.537 --> 01:19:05.472
I came here to make a grand
apology and I realized

01:19:05.474 --> 01:19:09.343
that that's still just me being

01:19:09.345 --> 01:19:10.377
in grand.

01:19:12.949 --> 01:19:13.881
But I'm not grand.

01:19:15.351 --> 01:19:19.520
There's a writer in this
room right now, though,

01:19:20.790 --> 01:19:24.525
and he's listened to my grand
ramblings for three days now.

01:19:25.394 --> 01:19:27.728
And that, he's listening.

01:19:30.132 --> 01:19:33.767
It taught me more than 50
years of my own bullshit.

01:19:35.972 --> 01:19:40.074
And so, let's all
listen to a short story

01:19:41.143 --> 01:19:42.376
from my good friend

01:19:43.512 --> 01:19:44.378
Greg.

01:20:10.106 --> 01:20:15.242
I actually have something
else that I'd like to read.

01:20:15.244 --> 01:20:16.410
I wrote this last night.

01:20:21.217 --> 01:20:24.451
I've never read this aloud
before, so here it goes.

01:20:26.622 --> 01:20:29.857
This is called, "To
Hell with Harvey".

01:20:31.961 --> 01:20:37.031
Warmth is an accident,
it is a thin atmosphere,

01:20:38.200 --> 01:20:41.435
much like on earth
it surrounds us.

01:20:41.437 --> 01:20:45.506
It is a flimsy shroud, invisible
and lighter than a feather.

01:20:47.310 --> 01:20:52.313
It may be our friends,
our family, and our hope.

01:20:53.482 --> 01:20:57.751
Thin and ephemeral,
and it can slip off us

01:20:57.753 --> 01:21:00.487
with a light force
of a cold drought.

01:21:01.657 --> 01:21:06.293
Some of us live without
it, live in the cold

01:21:06.295 --> 01:21:07.161
and we tremble.

01:21:09.165 --> 01:21:14.234
That is me, who I am if
exposed all the time.

01:21:15.438 --> 01:21:18.105
Everything hurts, but I
am convinced that I can

01:21:18.107 --> 01:21:21.842
restore that blanket, that
shroud if I just stand still.

01:21:22.979 --> 01:21:25.346
If I open myself
up to a stranger.

01:21:27.650 --> 01:21:29.350
If I try to be good.

01:21:30.987 --> 01:21:32.386
I doubt that I am good.

01:21:33.622 --> 01:21:36.156
I pray that one day I will
do something that brings

01:21:36.158 --> 01:21:37.024
people to me.

01:21:38.361 --> 01:21:39.193
Warmth,

01:21:40.663 --> 01:21:42.162
that's what will save me.

01:23:02.912 --> 01:23:04.411
What's this?

01:23:04.413 --> 01:23:07.347
Greg, I got a bad
habit of burning bridges,

01:23:07.349 --> 01:23:10.384
but one bridge I did not
burn was my publishers.

01:23:10.386 --> 01:23:13.454
And I gave her your
story, and she loved it.

01:23:13.456 --> 01:23:14.254
She did?

01:23:14.256 --> 01:23:15.689
Oh yeah she did.

01:23:15.691 --> 01:23:18.759
Her phone numbers in there,
so make sure you call her.

01:23:18.761 --> 01:23:20.761
You're a great writer, Greg.

01:23:20.763 --> 01:23:22.362
